---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About Me | The Cosmos Library">
  <div class="about-hero">
    <div class="about-hero-content">
      <div class="about-avatar">👨‍🚀</div>
      <h1>Nathanael King</h1>
      <p class="about-tagline">Army Reserve IT · Software Engineer · Space Enthusiast</p>
      <div class="about-badge-row">
        <span class="about-badge">🔧 25B IT Specialist</span>
        <span class="about-badge">🛠 Orbital Infrastructure</span>
        <span class="about-badge">📡 NASA APIs</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="about-body">

    <p class="about-intro">
      I'm the creator of the Cosmos Library — part blog, part resource hub, part portfolio.
      It's the place where I bring my vision of space exploration into one spot: the latest happenings,
      the tools I'm building, and the ideas that keep me up at night.
    </p>

    <div class="about-cards">

      <div class="about-card">
        <div class="about-card-icon">🌌</div>
        <h2>Why Space?</h2>
        <p>
          Space has fascinated me for as long as I can remember. The idea of exploration — of finding
          out where we fit in this cosmos, what our stewardship of this corner of the galaxy means for
          our eternal nature. The thought of seeing a whole new planet, or looking back at our solar
          system from somewhere entirely new, has always excited and terrified me in equal measure.
        </p>
        <p>
          The science and the potential feel just within reach. If I had to point to one vision of how
          humanity eventually gets there, it's <em>The Expanse</em> — gritty, realistic, and deeply human.
          That's the future I'm building toward.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-card">
        <div class="about-card-icon">🛰</div>
        <h2>What I'm Building</h2>
        <p>
          Rockets are too costly to be our only way out. The real answer is building <em>out there</em> —
          mining and gathering resources in space to fund the next step, and using drones and autonomous
          systems to lead the way before humans follow. I'm working on tools and concepts that explore
          that future: orbital infrastructure, real-time space data integrations, and software that makes
          the cosmos more accessible.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-card">
        <div class="about-card-icon">🔭</div>
        <h2>What's Next</h2>
        <p>
          Honestly? I don't fully know — and that's part of the fun. This site will grow as my ability
          to explore and test grows. Launch trackers, deeper NASA integrations, AI tools, more data from
          the edge of the solar system. Come back and see what's new.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="about-connect">
      <h2>Connect</h2>
      <div class="connect-grid">
        <a href="https://substack.com/@natdeviouswings" target="_blank" class="connect-card">
          <span class="connect-icon">📰</span>
          <span class="connect-label">Substack</span>
          <span class="connect-sub">Space writing & ideas</span>
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/DeviousWings" target="_blank" class="connect-card">
          <span class="connect-icon">💻</span>
          <span class="connect-label">GitHub</span>
          <span class="connect-sub">Code & projects</span>
        </a>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nathanaelkingitprofessional/" target="_blank" class="connect-card">
          <span class="connect-icon">🔗</span>
          <span class="connect-label">LinkedIn</span>
          <span class="connect-sub">Professional profile</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </section>
</Layout>
